[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bionic hand for gamer who lost arm to accident

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
James Young, who lost his arm and leg in an accident, has a prosthetic arm and bionic hand inspired by one of his favourite video games.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
31 March 2016 Last updated at 20:07 BST
The limb is based on one seen in Konami Digital Entertainment's Metal Gear Solid V: The Phantom Pain.
The 25-year-old was chosen by prosthetics artist Sophie De Oliviera Barata because of his positive attitude and love of video games.
